&lt;p&gt;Neurosurgical Unit&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Do you have an interest in Neurosurgery? Would you like to be involved in this specialised area ? Could you work alongside an innovative multidisciplinary team?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a very exciting opportunity for a Band 5 Registered Nurse to join our team. We can offer you a warm welcome to our unit on ward 228&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will have good communication skills. We are looking for a committed team player who has high standards and is passionate about improving the patient experience. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(Ward 228 is a 36 bedded unit, caring for patients with a variety of neurosurgical conditions including those stepping down from intensive care, or straight from theatres or A&amp;E, The ward based multidisciplinary team will care for patients requiring care following severe head trauma, complex spinal injuries, neurological tumours and other neurosurgical procedures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ward 228 needs you. If you think you are ready to work in our team, then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrie-Ann Smith, Senior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email Carrie-Ann.Smith@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
